@node LLM Execution Lifecycle
@chapter LLM Execution Lifecycle
@cindex LLM execution lifecycle
@cindex model execution
@cindex inference
@cindex cold-load
@cindex prefill
@cindex generation phase

This chapter explains exactly what happens inside Ollama from the moment
you press Enter to the moment characters appear on your screen.  It covers
every phase of a language model call --- loading, tokenizing, prefilling,
generating, streaming, idling, and unloading --- then walks the same example
prompt through both a non-thinking model and a thinking model so you can see
how differently they behave.

No machine-learning background is assumed.  Each concept is introduced from
first principles, with code snippets that show how Ollama and the model
libraries implement it.

